<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFE66A59F82697B11710B9FC" pageId="29" pageNumber="787" type="discussion">
Only recently described, but south-eastern China populations now attributed to this species were previously regarded as 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFE66A59F614946F1639B94D" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1915" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Tylonycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="787" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="robustula">7. robustula</taxonomicName>
